caption: If i could rate less than 1 star, trust me I would have today. My husband is a patient at Univ of Md and ordered by accident as this location doesn't deliver. Well, guess who couldn't reach a single person at that location since 12:30pm. Oh, and there's no other contact info..

This location is awful. I went in today and ordered a tuna sub. The lady didn’t put two scoops. She put one scoop and the smooth it out attempted to do a second scoop but the stopped and rudely looked up at me and said what do you want on it. I said can you put another scoop I eat at subway all the time this is unacceptable. She rudely replied an extra scoop is 70 cents. There is no way in the world she thought I was gonna pay extra for the normal portion. I said never mind and walked out the store. Worst subway experience ever!  Not to mention I was not greeted by anyone. They just said what kind of sandwich do you want. Very poor customer service and very scammy. They don’t give proper portions and want to over charge.

Stopped for breakfast... they were not busy, I had to use the restroom but it was locked with nobody in it. I politely asked them to unlock it, the man responded with "it's for customers". I said I really need to use it now please then I'll order, he said again barely audible "it's for customers" as he filled the lettuce bin with no gloves on mumbling something in a foreign language to the woman working with him. The last straw was when he was mumbling to himself, I asked him to speak up and clarify, he just looked at me and said nothing. So I told him what I thought of him and left. I really like subway, I've been to subways all over the country owned by all types of people and never had an experience like this, he chose to be rude and stingy. I hope he loses lots of business as a result of his actions. This location is clearly the problem avoid it if you can.
